      "content='{\"step_id\":3,\"reasoning\":\"The disassembly shows a clear loop from 0xffffffffc0d2729b to 0xffffffffc0d272aa: it loads a value from stall_duration_ms into rax, decrements it, and if not zero, jumps back to call __const_udelay. This is a delay loop that iterates stall_duration_ms times. The dmesg indicates the module started a stall simulation for 70000 ms. The crash occurred because the watchdog detected the CPU stuck in delay_tsc (called from __const_udelay) for 27 seconds, triggering a soft lockup. To confirm, I need to check the value of stall_duration_ms to see if it\\'s set to a large number causing a long delay. I\\'ll examine the module\\'s global variable stall_duration_ms.\",\"action\":{\"command_name\":\"rd\",\"arguments\":[\"0xffffffffc0d29058\"]},\"is_conclusive\":false,\"final_diagnosis\":null}' additional_kwargs={} response_metadata={} id='b0912c14-c270-485a-b2b1-b270db520c94' tool_calls=[{'name': 'rd', 'args': {'command': '0xffffffffc0d29058'}, 'id': 'call_3', 'type': 'tool_call'}] invalid_tool_calls=[]",
