      "content='{\"step_id\":4,\"reasoning\":\"The value at stall_duration_ms is 0x11170, which is 70000 in decimal. This matches the dmesg entry \\'Starting stall simulation for 70000 ms\\'. The loop iterates 70000 times, each time calling __const_udelay, which internally calls delay_tsc. This causes a long CPU stall, triggering the watchdog soft lockup after 27 seconds. The root cause is the third-party module rcu_stall_mod intentionally causing a delay that exceeds the watchdog threshold. I should also verify the loop is indeed infinite or long-running by checking the current loop counter value from the stack frame. I\\'ll examine the stack frame of rcu_stall_thread to see the local variable -0x40(%rbp) which holds the loop counter. First, I need to get the RSP value for the rcu_stall_thread frame from the backtrace. The backtrace shows RSP for frame #9 is ffff9a4cc5873eb0. I\\'ll use bt -f to dump the stack memory for that frame and locate the local variables.\",\"action\":{\"command_name\":\"bt\",\"arguments\":[\"-f\",\"ffff9a4cc5873eb0\"]},\"is_conclusive\":false,\"final_diagnosis\":null}' additional_kwargs={} response_metadata={} id='670081f6-0fa7-4042-b9ec-bc37ae8f8f8f' tool_calls=[{'name': 'bt', 'args': {'command': '-f ffff9a4cc5873eb0'}, 'id': 'call_4', 'type': 'tool_call'}] invalid_tool_calls=[]",
